{{!< default}}

<div class="container" style="padding-top:64px;padding-bottom:96px;">

  {{!-- Intro --}}
  <section class="about-intro">
    <div>
      <div class="about-photo about-photo--placeholder">
        {{#if @page.feature_image}}
          <img src="{{img_url @page.feature_image size="l"}}" alt="Chris MacDee" style="width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;border-radius:var(--radius-lg);">
        {{else}}
          Photo coming soon
        {{/if}}
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="about-bio">
      <h1>Hi, I'm Chris.</h1>
      <p>I make Henson-style puppets by hand and build software when I'm not elbow-deep in foam. Based in the UK, I've been making things — physical and digital — for as long as I can remember.</p>
      <p>My puppets are built in the tradition of Jim Henson's workshop: hand & rod puppets like Kermit and Gonzo, and live-hands puppets like Cookie Monster. Every piece is unique and made to commission.</p>
      <p>On the software side, I build whatever interests me — from personal life management tools to self-hosted infrastructure. This very site runs on a Raspberry Pi in my hallway.</p>
      <div class="hero__actions" style="justify-content:flex-start;margin-top:32px;">
        <a href="{{@site.url}}contact/?subject=commission" class="btn btn--primary">Commission a puppet</a>
        <a href="{{@site.url}}portfolio/" class="btn btn--outline">See my work</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {{!-- Disciplines --}}
  <h2 style="margin-bottom:24px;">What I make</h2>
  <div class="about-disciplines">
    <div class="discipline-card">
      <div class="discipline-card__icon">🎭</div>
      <h3 class="discipline-card__title">Henson-style Puppets</h3>
      <p class="discipline-card__desc">Hand &amp; rod puppets (Kermit, Gonzo style) and live-hands puppets (Cookie Monster, Swedish Chef style). Built from foam, fleece, and a lot of patience.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="discipline-card">
      <div class="discipline-card__icon">💻</div>
      <h3 class="discipline-card__title">Software &amp; Web Dev</h3>
      <p class="discipline-card__desc">Full-stack web applications, self-hosted services, and whatever rabbit hole I fell into this week. TypeScript, React, Node.js, Docker — the usual suspects.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  {{!-- Commission process --}}
  <h2 style="margin-bottom:8px;">How a commission works</h2>
  <p class="text-muted" style="margin-bottom:40px;">From first message to finished puppet, here's what to expect.</p>
  <div class="process-steps">
    <div class="process-step">
      <div class="process-step__number">1</div>
      <h4 class="process-step__title">Get in touch</h4>
      <p class="process-step__desc">Tell me what you're after. Character reference, style, size, intended use — the more detail the better.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="process-step">
      <div class="process-step__number">2</div>
      <h4 class="process-step__title">Discuss &amp; quote</h4>
      <p class="process-step__desc">We'll work out the details and I'll give you a quote. Deposit required before build begins.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="process-step">
      <div class="process-step__number">3</div>
      <h4 class="process-step__title">Build &amp; check in</h4>
      <p class="process-step__desc">I'll build your puppet and send progress photos at key stages. Your feedback shapes the final piece.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="process-step">
      <div class="process-step__number">4</div>
      <h4 class="process-step__title">Delivery</h4>
      <p class="process-step__desc">Final payment, then your puppet is carefully packed and shipped. A build log post goes up on the blog.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  {{> commission-strip}}
</div>
